1. Definitions

"Licensed Materials" means this repository, source code, documentation, user
interface text, assets, and any distributed copies.

"Application Use" means using the working browser application through a hosted
page or a local copy for recording, note-taking, testing, demonstration,
personal use, professional use, or internal workflow use.

"AI/ML Use" means using the Licensed Materials, or any portion of them, as
training data, fine-tuning data, evaluation data, benchmark data, retrieval
corpus, embeddings input, synthetic-data seed, model-output comparison target,
or any other input to develop, train, tune, evaluate, improve, or operate a
machine learning or artificial intelligence system.

"Automated Extraction" means scraping, crawling, bulk downloading, mirroring,
mining, parsing, copying, or otherwise extracting the Licensed Materials using
automated or semi-automated means.

2. Permission for application users

You may use the application as a user. This includes:

- accessing the public hosted version;
- running an unmodified local copy;
- using the application output for your own lawful purposes;
- sharing a link to the original project or hosted application.

